# AIV Integrity Gate (maintainer + agent)

## Releases

- After changing the reactor **`<version>`** in the root `pom.xml`, run **`scripts/sync-action-version.ps1`** (Windows) or **`scripts/sync-action-version.sh`** (Git Bash / Linux) so **`action.yml`** `inputs.aiv-version` default matches Central.
- GitHub **Marketplace** listing text is edited in the GitHub UI when publishing the action; it is not only `action.yml`.

## Machine-readable output

- **`--output-json`**: consumers must check **`doctor_mode`**. When **`doctor_mode` is `true`**, **`passed`** does not imply a normal CI gate pass (informational `doctor` run).
- **`--output-sarif`**: same distinction via **`runs[].properties.doctorMode`**.
- **`schema_version`** in JSON is documented in **CHANGELOG.md**; breaking JSON shape changes require a changelog entry and version bump policy.

## Tests and coverage

- Parent POM enforces **100% line** JaCoCo on **`mvn verify`**. New code paths need tests in the same module.
- Prefer **package-private** test hooks over **reflection** for adapter internals.

## Product boundaries (not implied by this repo)

- **Security gate**, **baseline suppressions**, and **labeled benchmarks** are roadmap items unless a module ships in-tree.

## Commits

- Do not rely on repo code to strip **local git hook** trailers (e.g. tool attribution). Configure **`.git/hooks`** or `core.hooksPath` locally if needed.
